+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BQUvhSBTVXTgKjx5RPY3ni","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the entire project. Here's a comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts              (Database setup & seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts          (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts          (Express routes for CRUD)\n│   ├── errors.ts          (Error handling)\n│   ├── server.ts          (Express app factory)\n│   └── seed.ts            (Database seeding script)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts      (CRUD tests)\n│   └── search.test.ts     (Full-text search tests)\n├── package.json           (Dependencies & scripts)\n├── tsconfig.json          (TypeScript config)\n├── vitest.config.ts       (Testing framework config)\n└── .eslintrc.cjs          (Linting config)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. package.json\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- ES modules enabled (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- Core: Express 4.21 + better-sqlite3 11.0\n- Testing: Vitest 2.0 + Supertest 7.0\n- Scripts: build, lint, test, seed\n\n---\n\n### 3. tsconfig.json\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Generates source maps and declaration files\n- Excludes tests from build\n\n---\n\n### 4. src/db.ts - Database Setup\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createDatabase(path?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = path ? new Database(path) : new Database(':memory:');\n\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  // Create notes table\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      title TEXT NOT NULL,\n      body TEXT NOT NULL,\n      tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n      created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n      updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport function seedDatabase(db: Database.Database): void {\n  const insert = db.prepare(`\n    INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n  `);\n\n  const notes = getSeedNotes();\n\n  const insertMany = db.transaction((items: { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[]) => {\n    for (const item of items) {\n      insert.run(item.title, item.body, item.tags);\n    }\n  });\n\n  insertMany(notes);\n}\n\nfunction getSeedNotes(): { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[] {\n  return [\n    {\n      title: 'Getting Started with TypeScript',\n      body: 'TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. It adds optional static typing and class-based object-oriented programming to the language. TypeScript is designed for development of large applications and transcompiles to JavaScript.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'typescript', 'javascript']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Introduction to Python Programming',\n      body: 'Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It supports multiple programming paradigms including procedural, object-oriented, and functional programming. Python is widely used in web development, data science, and automation.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'python']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Understanding Database Indexing',\n      body: 'Database indexing is a data structure technique used to quickly locate and access data in a database. Indexes are created using columns that are frequently searched against. Without an index, the database must scan every row to find relevant data, which becomes slow for large tables.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['database', 'performance']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Homemade Pasta Recipe',\n      body: 'Making fresh pasta at home is surprisingly simple. You need flour, eggs, salt, and olive oil. Mix the ingredients to form a dough, knead for 10 minutes until smooth, rest for 30 minutes, then roll out and cut into your desired shape. Cook in boiling salted water for 2-3 minutes.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'recipes', 'italian']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies',\n      body: 'The perfect chocolate chip cookie requires butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, flour, baking soda, salt, and chocolate chips. Cream the butter and sugars, add eggs and vanilla, mix in dry ingredients, fold in chocolate chips, and bake at 375°F for 9-11 minutes.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'recipes', 'baking']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Travel Guide: Tokyo Japan',\n      body: 'Tokyo is a fascinating blend of ultramodern and traditional. Visit the ancient Senso-ji temple, explore the bustling streets of Shibuya, enjoy fresh sushi at Tsukiji fish market, and experience the tranquility of Meiji Shrine. The best time to visit is during cherry blossom season in spring.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'japan', 'asia']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Exploring Paris France',\n      body: 'Paris, the City of Light, offers world-class museums like the Louvre, iconic landmarks like the Eiffel Tower, charming neighborhoods like Montmartre, and exquisite cuisine. Stroll along the Seine, visit Notre-Dame Cathedral, and enjoy croissants at a sidewalk cafe.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'france', 'europe']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Quantum Computing Basics',\n      body: 'Quantum computing leverages quantum mechanical phenomena like superposition and entanglement to process information. Unlike classical bits that are either 0 or 1, quantum bits (qubits) can exist in multiple states simultaneously. This enables quantum computers to solve certain problems exponentially faster.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'computing', 'physics']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'The Solar System Overview',\n      body: 'Our solar system consists of the Sun and everything that orbits it, including eight planets, dwarf planets, moons, asteroids, and comets. The inner planets (Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars) are rocky, while the outer planets (Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune) are gas or ice giants.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'astronomy', 'space']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Learning Guitar for Beginners',\n      body: 'Starting guitar requires patience and practice. Begin with basic open chords like G, C, D, E minor, and A minor. Practice transitioning between chords smoothly. Learn simple strumming patterns and work on finger strength. Playing just 15 minutes daily will show remarkable progress within weeks.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['music', 'guitar', 'learning']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'History of Jazz Music',\n      body: 'Jazz originated in the African-American communities of New Orleans in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. It blends elements of blues, ragtime, and European harmony. Key figures include Louis Armstrong, Duke Ellington, Charlie Parker, and Miles Davis. Jazz has evolved through many styles including swing, bebop, and fusion.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['music', 'history', 'jazz']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'React Hooks Deep Dive',\n      body: 'React Hooks allow you to use state and other React features without writing class components. useState manages local state, useEffect handles side effects, useContext accesses context, and useMemo optimizes performance. Custom hooks let you extract reusable stateful logic.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'react', 'javascript']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Docker Container Essentials',\n      body: 'Docker containers package applications with their dependencies into standardized units for development, shipment, and deployment. Containers are lightweight, portable, and consistent across environments. Key concepts include images, containers, volumes, networks, and docker-compose for multi-container applications.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'devops', 'docker']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Mediterranean Diet Benefits',\n      body: 'The Mediterranean diet emphasizes fruits, vegetables, whole grains, legumes, nuts, and olive oil. It includes moderate amounts of fish, poultry, and dairy, with limited red meat. Studies show it reduces risk of heart disease, stroke, type 2 diabetes, and cognitive decline.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'nutrition', 'diet']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Yoga for Stress Relief',\n      body: 'Yoga combines physical postures, breathing exercises, and meditation to promote relaxation and reduce stress. Regular practice improves flexibility, strength, and mental clarity. Beginner-friendly poses include child pose, downward dog, warrior I and II, and tree pose.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'fitness', 'yoga']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Machine Learning Fundamentals',\n      body: 'Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence where algorithms learn patterns from data without being explicitly programmed. Key types include supervised learning (classification, regression), unsupervised learning (clustering), and reinforcement learning. Popular frameworks include TensorFlow, PyTorch, and scikit-learn.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'ai', 'machine-learning']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Backpacking Through Southeast Asia',\n      body: 'Southeast Asia offers incredible backpacking experiences on a budget. Visit ancient temples in Cambodia, pristine beaches in Thailand, rice terraces in Vietnam, and vibrant cities in Malaysia. Budget around $30-50 per day for accommodation, food, and transport.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'asia', 'backpacking']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Sourdough Bread Baking Guide',\n      body: 'Sourdough bread requires a mature starter, flour, water, and salt. The process involves mixing, autolyse, bulk fermentation with stretch and folds, shaping, cold retard overnight, and baking in a Dutch oven. The natural fermentation creates complex flavors and better digestibility.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'baking', 'bread']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Introduction to Rust Programming',\n      body: 'Rust is a systems programming language focused on safety, speed, and concurrency. Its ownership system prevents null pointer dereferences, dangling pointers, and data races at compile time. Rust is ideal for performance-critical applications, web assembly, and embedded systems.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'rust', 'systems']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Climate Change and Renewable Energy',\n      body: 'Renewable energy sources like solar, wind, hydroelectric, and geothermal are essential for combating climate change. Solar panel costs have dropped 89% since 2010. Wind energy is the fastest-growing power source globally. Transitioning to renewables can significantly reduce greenhouse gas emissions.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'environment', 'energy']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Photography Composition Techniques',\n      body: 'Great photography relies on strong composition. The rule of thirds places subjects at grid intersections. Leading lines guide the viewer eye. Framing uses natural elements to surround the subject. Symmetry creates balance. Negative space emphasizes the main subject by leaving empty areas.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['photography', 'art', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'GraphQL vs REST API Design',\n      body: 'GraphQL lets clients request exactly the data they need in a single query, reducing over-fetching and under-fetching common with REST. REST uses multiple endpoints with fixed data structures. GraphQL has a single endpoint with a flexible query language. Both have tradeoffs in caching, complexity, and tooling.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'api', 'web']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'The Art of French Cooking',\n      body: 'French cuisine is built on foundational techniques: the five mother sauces (bechamel, veloute, espagnole, hollandaise, tomato), proper knife skills, stock making, and mastering heat control. Classic dishes include coq au vin, beef bourguignon, ratatouille, and creme brulee.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'french', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Hiking the Appalachian Trail',\n      body: 'The Appalachian Trail stretches 2,190 miles from Georgia to Maine through 14 states. Thru-hiking takes 5-7 months. Section hiking is popular for those with less time. Essential gear includes a quality backpack, lightweight tent, sleeping bag, water filter, and proper hiking boots.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'hiking', 'outdoors']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Kubernetes Orchestration Guide',\n      body: 'Kubernetes automates deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications. Key concepts include pods, services, deployments, namespaces, and ingress controllers. Kubernetes provides self-healing, horizontal scaling, rolling updates, and service discovery out of the box.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'devops', 'kubernetes']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Classical Music Appreciation',\n      body: 'Classical music spans centuries from Bach and Handel through Mozart and Beethoven to modern composers. The orchestra typically includes strings, woodwinds, brass, and percussion sections. Major forms include symphonies, concertos, sonatas, and operas. Listening actively to different sections enhances appreciation.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['music', 'classical', 'culture']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Effective Public Speaking',\n      body: 'Great public speakers master preparation, delivery, and audience engagement. Structure talks with a hook, three main points, and a memorable closing. Use pauses for emphasis, vary your tone, maintain eye contact, and use gestures naturally. Practice extensively and seek feedback.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['communication', 'skills', 'career']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Indoor Plant Care Essentials',\n      body: 'Successful indoor gardening requires understanding light, water, and soil needs. Low-light plants like pothos and snake plants are great for beginners. Water when the top inch of soil is dry. Use well-draining potting mix. Fertilize monthly during growing season. Monitor for pests regularly.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['gardening', 'plants', 'home']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'SQLite Full-Text Search Tutorial',\n      body: 'SQLite FTS5 provides powerful full-text search capabilities. Create a virtual table using FTS5, insert content, and query using the MATCH operator. FTS5 supports phrase queries, prefix queries, boolean operators, and ranking with BM25. Snippet extraction highlights matching terms in results.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'database', 'sqlite']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Mindfulness Meditation Practice',\n      body: 'Mindfulness meditation involves focusing attention on the present moment without judgment. Start with 5-minute sessions, focusing on breath. When thoughts arise, acknowledge them and return to breathing. Regular practice reduces anxiety, improves focus, and promotes emotional resilience.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'meditation', 'wellness']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Web Accessibility Standards',\n      body: 'Web accessibility ensures websites are usable by people with disabilities. Follow WCAG guidelines: provide alt text for images, ensure keyboard navigation, use semantic HTML, maintain sufficient color contrast, add ARIA labels, and test with screen readers. Accessibility benefits all users.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'web', 'accessibility']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Italian Risotto Masterclass',\n      body: 'Perfect risotto requires Arborio or Carnaroli rice, warm stock, patience, and constant stirring. Toast the rice in butter, add wine, then ladle warm stock gradually while stirring. The starch releases slowly, creating a creamy texture. Finish with butter and Parmigiano-Reggiano.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'italian', 'recipes']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Artificial Neural Networks Explained',\n      body: 'Neural networks are computing systems inspired by biological neural networks. They consist of layers of interconnected nodes (neurons) that process information. Deep learning uses many hidden layers to learn hierarchical representations. Applications include image recognition, natural language processing, and autonomous vehicles.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'ai', 'deep-learning']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Sustainable Living Tips',\n      body: 'Reduce your environmental footprint by minimizing single-use plastics, composting food waste, choosing renewable energy, buying local produce, reducing water usage, and using public transport or cycling. Small daily choices collectively make a significant environmental impact.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['environment', 'lifestyle', 'sustainability']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Chess Strategy for Intermediates',\n      body: 'Improve your chess by studying openings, understanding pawn structure, controlling the center, developing pieces early, and thinking several moves ahead. Learn tactical patterns like pins, forks, skewers, and discovered attacks. Analyze your games to identify mistakes and patterns.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['games', 'chess', 'strategy']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'RESTful API Best Practices',\n      body: 'Design RESTful APIs with consistent naming conventions, proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE), meaningful status codes, pagination for collections, versioning, authentication, and comprehensive error responses. Use JSON for request and response bodies. Document with OpenAPI specification.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'api', 'rest']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Nordic Hiking Adventures',\n      body: 'Scandinavia offers breathtaking hiking through fjords, mountains, and arctic landscapes. Norway Trolltunga and Preikestolen are iconic. Sweden Kungsleden trail spans 270 miles. Finland offers midnight sun hiking in summer. Pack layers, waterproof gear, and be prepared for rapidly changing weather.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'hiking', 'europe']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Espresso Brewing Techniques',\n      body: 'Perfect espresso requires freshly roasted beans, proper grind size, correct dose (18-20g), consistent tamping pressure, water temperature around 200°F, and 25-30 second extraction time. The result should be a balanced shot with a rich crema layer. Adjust grind size to control flow rate.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'coffee', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Version Control with Git',\n      body: 'Git is the most widely used version control system. Key commands include init, clone, add, commit, push, pull, branch, merge, and rebase. Use feature branches for development, pull requests for code review, and tags for releases. Write meaningful commit messages that explain why changes were made.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'git', 'tools']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'The Science of Sleep',\n      body: 'Quality sleep is essential for health. Adults need 7-9 hours nightly. Sleep cycles through stages including light sleep, deep sleep, and REM. Improve sleep hygiene by maintaining consistent schedules, limiting screen time before bed, keeping rooms cool and dark, and avoiding caffeine after noon.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'science', 'sleep']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Watercolor Painting Basics',\n      body: 'Watercolor painting uses water-soluble pigments on paper. Start with basic techniques: wet-on-wet for soft blends, wet-on-dry for sharp edges, and dry brush for texture. Use quality paper (140lb cold press), a limited palette of primary colors, and practice controlling water ratios.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['art', 'painting', 'watercolor']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Blockchain Technology Overview',\n      body: 'Blockchain is a distributed ledger technology where data is stored in linked blocks secured by cryptography. Each block contains a hash of the previous block, creating an immutable chain. Applications extend beyond cryptocurrency to supply chain, healthcare records, and voting systems.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['technology', 'blockchain', 'crypto']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Thai Cooking Fundamentals',\n      body: 'Thai cuisine balances sweet, sour, salty, spicy, and bitter flavors. Essential ingredients include fish sauce, lime, lemongrass, galangal, Thai basil, and coconut milk. Master dishes like pad thai, green curry, tom yum soup, and mango sticky rice. Fresh herbs and aromatics are key.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'thai', 'asian']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Astrophotography Guide',\n      body: 'Capturing the night sky requires a DSLR or mirrorless camera, wide-angle lens, sturdy tripod, and remote shutter release. Use manual mode with wide aperture (f/2.8 or lower), high ISO (1600-6400), and long exposure (15-30 seconds). The 500 rule helps avoid star trails.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['photography', 'astronomy', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Functional Programming Concepts',\n      body: 'Functional programming treats computation as evaluation of mathematical functions. Core concepts include pure functions, immutability, higher-order functions, function composition, and avoiding side effects. Languages like Haskell, Elixir, and Clojure embrace FP, while JavaScript and Python support FP patterns.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'functional', 'concepts']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Home Coffee Roasting',\n      body: 'Roasting coffee at home gives you control over flavor profiles. Green beans progress through drying, first crack, development, and optionally second crack. Light roasts preserve origin flavors, medium roasts balance sweetness and body, dark roasts emphasize roast character. Cool beans quickly after roasting.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'coffee', 'hobby']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Climbing Mount Kilimanjaro',\n      body: 'Kilimanjaro is the highest peak in Africa at 19,341 feet. The Machame route is the most scenic, taking 6-7 days. Acclimatization is crucial to prevent altitude sickness. No technical climbing skills needed, but physical fitness is essential. The summit offers breathtaking views of the African plains.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'hiking', 'africa']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'CSS Grid Layout Mastery',\n      body: 'CSS Grid provides a two-dimensional layout system for the web. Define rows and columns with grid-template, place items with grid-column and grid-row, and use gap for spacing. Grid areas name regions for intuitive placement. Combine with Flexbox for complete layout control.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'css', 'web']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Fermentation and Pickling',\n      body: 'Fermentation preserves food using beneficial bacteria. Sauerkraut, kimchi, kombucha, and yogurt are popular fermented foods. Basic lacto-fermentation needs only vegetables, salt, and water. Maintain proper salt ratios (2-3%), keep vegetables submerged, and ferment at room temperature for optimal results.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'fermentation', 'preservation']),\n    },\n  ];\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Creates SQLite database (file or in-memory)\n- WAL mode enabled for concurrency\n- Foreign keys enabled\n- Seeds 45 notes across diverse categories\n- Uses database transactions for bulk insert\n\n---\n\n### 5. src/models.ts - Type Definitions\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Note: Full note object from DB\n- NoteInput: For POST/PUT requests\n- SearchResult: Search response structure\n- SuggestResult: Autocomplete suggestions\n\n---\n\n### 6. src/routes.ts - Express Routes\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { Note, NoteInput } from './models.js';\nimport { NotFoundError, ValidationError } from './errors.js';\n\nexport function createRoutes(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // GET /notes - List all notes (with optional tag filter)\n  router.get('/notes', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const tag = req.query.tag as string | undefined;\n\n      let notes: Note[];\n      if (tag) {\n        // Use a join with json_each for tag filtering\n        const tagStmt = db.prepare(`\n          SELECT DISTINCT notes.* FROM notes, json_each(notes.tags)\n          WHERE json_each.value = ?\n          ORDER BY created_at DESC\n        `);\n        notes = tagStmt.all(tag) as Note[];\n      } else {\n        const stmt = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes ORDER BY created_at DESC');\n        notes = stmt.all() as Note[];\n      }\n\n      res.json({ notes });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // GET /notes/:id - Get single note\n  router.get('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const stmt = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?');\n      const note = stmt.get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!note) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      res.json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // POST /notes - Create note\n  router.post('/notes', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const input = req.body as NoteInput;\n\n      if (!input.title || input.title.trim() === '') {\n        throw new ValidationError('Title is required');\n      }\n      if (!input.body || input.body.trim() === '') {\n        throw new ValidationError('Body is required');\n      }\n\n      const tags = input.tags ? JSON.stringify(input.tags) : '[]';\n      const stmt = db.prepare(`\n        INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n      `);\n      const result = stmt.run(input.title, input.body, tags);\n\n      const note = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(result.lastInsertRowid) as Note;\n      res.status(201).json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // PUT /notes/:id - Update note\n  router.put('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const existing = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!existing) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      const input = req.body as Partial<NoteInput>;\n      const title = input.title ?? existing.title;\n      const body = input.body ?? existing.body;\n      const tags = input.tags ? JSON.stringify(input.tags) : existing.tags;\n\n      const stmt = db.prepare(`\n        UPDATE notes SET title = ?, body = ?, tags = ?, updated_at = datetime('now')\n        WHERE id = ?\n      `);\n      stmt.run(title, body, tags, id);\n\n      const note = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note;\n      res.json({ note });\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // DELETE /notes/:id - Delete note\n  router.delete('/notes/:id', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n    try {\n      const id = parseInt(req.params.id);\n      const existing = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM notes WHERE id = ?').get(id) as Note | undefined;\n\n      if (!existing) {\n        throw new NotFoundError('Note not found');\n      }\n\n      db.prepare('DELETE FROM notes WHERE id = ?').run(id);\n      res.status(204).send();\n    } catch (err) {\n      next(err);\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**CRUD Operations:**\n- GET /notes - List with optional tag filter (uses json_each)\n- GET /notes/:id - Get single note\n- POST /notes - Create (validates title/body)\n- PUT /notes/:id - Update (partial updates)\n- DELETE /notes/:id - Delete\n- All error-wrapped in try/catch with next(err)\n\n---\n\n### 7. src/errors.ts - Error Handling\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nimport { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\n\nexport class NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n  constructor(message = 'Resource not found') {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'NotFoundError';\n  }\n}\n\nexport class ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n  constructor(message = 'Validation failed') {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'ValidationError';\n  }\n}\n\nexport function errorHandler(\n  err: Error,\n  _req: Request,\n  res: Response,\n  _next: NextFunction\n): void {\n  if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {\n    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });\n  } else if (err instanceof ValidationError) {\n    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });\n  } else {\n    console.error(err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Custom NotFoundError (404)\n- Custom ValidationError (400)\n- Express error handler middleware\n- Catches unknown errors (500)\n\n---\n\n### 8. src/server.ts - Express App Factory\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createDatabase, seedDatabase } from './db.js';\nimport { createRoutes } from './routes.js';\nimport { errorHandler } from './errors.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface App {\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  const db = createDatabase(dbPath);\n  const app = express();\n\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const routes = createRoutes(db);\n  app.use(routes);\n\n  app.use(errorHandler);\n\n  return { app, db };\n}\n\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  const { app, db } = createApp(dbPath);\n  seedDatabase(db);\n  return { app, db };\n}\n\n// Start server if run directly\nconst isMain = process.argv[1]?.endsWith('server.js') || process.argv[1]?.endsWith('server.ts');\nif (isMain) {\n  const { app } = createSeededApp();\n  const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;\n  app.listen(port, () => {\n    console.log(`Server running on port ${port}`);\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- createApp: Bare app factory\n- createSeededApp: With 45 pre-populated notes\n- Can run standalone on PORT (default 3000)\n- Returns {app, db} pair for testing\n\n---\n\n### 9. src/seed.ts - Seeding Script\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nimport { createDatabase, seedDatabase } from './db.js';\n\nconst dbPath = process.argv[2] || 'notes.db';\nconsole.log(`Seeding database at: ${dbPath}`);\n\nconst db = createDatabase(dbPath);\nseedDatabase(db);\n\nconst count = (db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM notes').get() as { count: number }).count;\nconsole.log(`Seeded ${count} notes successfully.`);\n\ndb.close();\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- CLI seed script\n- Accepts DB path as argument\n- Logs count of seeded notes\n\n---\n\n### 10. tests/notes.test.ts - CRUD Tests\n\n**Complete Contents (15 tests):**\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\nimport type { App } from '../src/server.js';\n\ndescribe('Notes CRUD', () => {\n  let appCtx: App;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    appCtx = createApp();\n  });\n\n  afterEach(() => {\n    appCtx.db.close();\n  });\n\n  // 1. GET /notes returns all notes\n  it('GET /notes returns all notes', async () => {\n    appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body) VALUES ('Note 1', 'Body 1')\").run();\n    appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body) VALUES ('Note 2', 'Body 2')\").run();\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.notes).toHaveLength(2);\n  });\n\n  // 2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n  it('GET /notes/:id returns specific note', async () => {\n    const result = appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body) VALUES ('Test Note', 'Test Body')\").run();\n    const id = result.lastInsertRowid;\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get(`/notes/${id}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.note.title).toBe('Test Note');\n    expect(res.body.note.body).toBe('Test Body');\n  });\n\n  // 3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n  it('GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/9999');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n\n  // 4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n  it('POST /notes creates note with title and body', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'New Note', body: 'New Body' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.note.title).toBe('New Note');\n    expect(res.body.note.body).toBe('New Body');\n    expect(res.body.note.id).toBeDefined();\n  });\n\n  // 5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n  it('POST /notes creates note with tags', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Tagged Note', body: 'Body', tags: ['test', 'vitest'] });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    const tags = JSON.parse(res.body.note.tags);\n    expect(tags).toContain('test');\n    expect(tags).toContain('vitest');\n  });\n\n  // 6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n  it('POST /notes returns 400 without title', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ body: 'Body only' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n\n  // 7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n  it('POST /notes returns 400 without body', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Title only' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n\n  // 8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n  it('PUT /notes/:id updates note', async () => {\n    const result = appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body) VALUES ('Original', 'Original body')\").run();\n    const id = result.lastInsertRowid;\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .put(`/notes/${id}`)\n      .send({ title: 'Updated', body: 'Updated body' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.note.title).toBe('Updated');\n    expect(res.body.note.body).toBe('Updated body');\n  });\n\n  // 9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n  it('PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .put('/notes/9999')\n      .send({ title: 'Updated' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n\n  // 10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n  it('DELETE /notes/:id removes note', async () => {\n    const result = appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body) VALUES ('To Delete', 'Body')\").run();\n    const id = result.lastInsertRowid;\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).delete(`/notes/${id}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(204);\n\n    // Verify deletion\n    const getRes = await request(appCtx.app).get(`/notes/${id}`);\n    expect(getRes.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n\n  // 11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n  it('DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).delete('/notes/9999');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n\n  // 12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n  it('GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag', async () => {\n    appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES ('Tagged', 'Body', ?)\")\n      .run(JSON.stringify(['javascript', 'testing']));\n    appCtx.db.prepare(\"INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES ('Other', 'Body', ?)\")\n      .run(JSON.stringify(['python']));\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes?tag=javascript');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.notes).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(res.body.notes[0].title).toBe('Tagged');\n  });\n\n  // 13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n  it('Notes have created_at timestamp', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Timestamped', body: 'Body' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.note.created_at).toBeDefined();\n    expect(typeof res.body.note.created_at).toBe('string');\n  });\n\n  // 14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n  it('Notes have updated_at timestamp', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Timestamped', body: 'Body' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.note.updated_at).toBeDefined();\n    expect(typeof res.body.note.updated_at).toBe('string');\n  });\n\n  // 15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n  it('PUT updates updated_at timestamp', async () => {\n    appCtx.db.prepare(\n      \"INSERT INTO notes (title, body, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('Old', 'Body', '2020-01-01 00:00:00', '2020-01-01 00:00:00')\"\n    ).run();\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .put('/notes/1')\n      .send({ title: 'Updated Title' });\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.note.updated_at).not.toBe('2020-01-01 00:00:00');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- List notes (GET /notes)\n- Get single note (GET /notes/:id)\n- Create note (POST /notes)\n- Create with tags\n- Create validation\n- Update note (PUT /notes/:id)\n- Delete note (DELETE /notes/:id)\n- Tag filtering (GET /notes?tag=X)\n- Timestamps (created_at, updated_at)\n\n---\n\n### 11. tests/search.test.ts - Full-Text Search Tests\n\n**Complete Contents (20 tests):**\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createSeededApp } from '../src/server.js';\nimport type { App } from '../src/server.js';\n\ndescribe('Search', () => {\n  let appCtx: App;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    appCtx = createSeededApp();\n  });\n\n  afterEach(() => {\n    appCtx.db.close();\n  });\n\n  // 1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n  it('GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=python');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n  });\n\n  // 2. GET /notes/search?q=keyword results have snippet field\n  it('GET /notes/search?q=keyword results have snippet field', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=python');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results[0]).toHaveProperty('snippet');\n    expect(typeof res.body.results[0].snippet).toBe('string');\n  });\n\n  // 3. Snippets contain <mark> tags around matched terms\n  it('Snippets contain <mark> tags around matched terms', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=python');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    const snippet = res.body.results[0].snippet;\n    expect(snippet).toContain('<mark>');\n    expect(snippet).toContain('</mark>');\n  });\n\n  // 4. Results are ranked by relevance (most relevant first)\n  it('Results are ranked by relevance (most relevant first)', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=programming');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeGreaterThan(1);\n    // rank values should be in ascending order (lower rank = more relevant in FTS5)\n    for (let i = 1; i < res.body.results.length; i++) {\n      expect(res.body.results[i].rank).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(res.body.results[i - 1].rank);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // 5. GET /notes/search?q=\"exact phrase\" matches exact phrases\n  it('GET /notes/search?q=\"exact phrase\" matches exact phrases', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=\"chocolate chip\"');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n    const titles = res.body.results.map((r: { title: string }) => r.title);\n    expect(titles.some((t: string) => t.toLowerCase().includes('chocolate'))).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  // 6. Search returns id, title, snippet, rank fields\n  it('Search returns id, title, snippet, rank fields', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=guitar');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n    const result = res.body.results[0];\n    expect(result).toHaveProperty('id');\n    expect(result).toHaveProperty('title');\n    expect(result).toHaveProperty('snippet');\n    expect(result).toHaveProperty('rank');\n    expect(typeof result.id).toBe('number');\n    expect(typeof result.title).toBe('string');\n    expect(typeof result.snippet).toBe('string');\n    expect(typeof result.rank).toBe('number');\n  });\n\n  // 7. GET /notes/search?q=nonexistent returns empty array\n  it('GET /notes/search?q=nonexistent returns empty array', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=xyznonexistentterm');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results).toEqual([]);\n  });\n\n  // 8. GET /notes/search without q returns 400\n  it('GET /notes/search without q returns 400', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n\n  // 9. GET /notes/search?q= (empty) returns 400\n  it('GET /notes/search?q= (empty) returns 400', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n\n  // 10. Pagination: page=1 returns first 20 results\n  it('Pagination: page=1 returns first 20 results', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=the&page=1');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeLessThanOrEqual(20);\n    expect(res.body.page).toBe(1);\n    expect(res.body.perPage).toBe(20);\n  });\n\n  // 11. Pagination: page=2 returns next results\n  it('Pagination: page=2 returns next results', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=the&page=2');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.page).toBe(2);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body.results)).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  // 12. Pagination response includes total count\n  it('Pagination response includes total count', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=programming');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body).toHaveProperty('total');\n    expect(typeof res.body.total).toBe('number');\n    expect(res.body.total).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n  });\n\n  // 13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n  it('GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search/suggest?q=learn');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(Array.isArray(res.body.results)).toBe(true);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeLessThanOrEqual(5);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n  });\n\n  // 14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n  it('Suggest results match prefix in title', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search/suggest?q=getting');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n    const titles = res.body.results.map((r: { title: string }) => r.title.toLowerCase());\n    expect(titles.some((t: string) => t.includes('getting'))).toBe(true);\n  });\n\n  // 15. GET /notes/search/suggest?q= returns 400\n  it('GET /notes/search/suggest?q= returns 400', async () => {\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search/suggest?q=');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n\n  // 16. FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search\n  it('FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search', async () => {\n    await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Zylophone Dynamics', body: 'The zylophone produces unique harmonics and overtones.' });\n\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=zylophone');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.results.length).toBe(1);\n    expect(res.body.results[0].title).toBe('Zylophone Dynamics');\n  });\n\n  // 17. FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search\n  it('FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search', async () => {\n    const createRes = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Original Title', body: 'Original content about elephants.' });\n    const noteId = createRes.body.note.id;\n\n    await request(appCtx.app)\n      .put(`/notes/${noteId}`)\n      .send({ title: 'Updated Title', body: 'Updated content about xylographics.' });\n\n    const searchNew = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=xylographics');\n    expect(searchNew.body.results.length).toBe(1);\n\n    const searchOld = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=elephants');\n    expect(searchOld.body.results.length).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  // 18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n  it('FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search', async () => {\n    const createRes = await request(appCtx.app)\n      .post('/notes')\n      .send({ title: 'Temporary Note', body: 'Quizzaciously unique content for deletion test.' });\n    const noteId = createRes.body.note.id;\n\n    let searchRes = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=quizzaciously');\n    expect(searchRes.body.results.length).toBe(1);\n\n    await request(appCtx.app).delete(`/notes/${noteId}`);\n\n    searchRes = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=quizzaciously');\n    expect(searchRes.body.results.length).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  // 19. Special characters in query don't crash\n  it(\"Special characters in query don't crash\", async () => {\n    const specialQueries = [\n      '/notes/search?q=hello%20world',\n      '/notes/search?q=test%26test',\n      '/notes/search?q=it%27s',\n      '/notes/search?q=%3Cscript%3E',\n      '/notes/search?q=foo%2Bbar',\n      '/notes/search?q=a%2Fb',\n    ];\n\n    for (const url of specialQueries) {\n      const res = await request(appCtx.app).get(url);\n      expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n      expect(Array.isArray(res.body.results)).toBe(true);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // 20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n  it('Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset', async () => {\n    const start = performance.now();\n    const res = await request(appCtx.app).get('/notes/search?q=programming');\n    const elapsed = performance.now() - start;\n\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(elapsed).toBeLessThan(100);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Search Features Tested (Expected):**\n- Keyword search (GET /notes/search?q=keyword)\n- Snippet generation with `<mark>` highlighting\n- Relevance ranking (FTS5 BM25)\n- Exact phrase queries\n- Field structure (id, title, snippet, rank)\n- Empty query validation\n- Pagination (page, perPage, total)\n- Autocomplete suggestions (GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix)\n- FTS5 sync on create/update/delete\n- Special character handling\n- Performance (< 100ms)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **benchmark/feature evaluation project** for SQLite FTS5 (Full-Text Search) integration in Express.js. Key observations:\n\n1. **Current State**: Only basic CRUD operations are implemented in routes.ts\n2. **Missing**: All search endpoints (GET /notes/search, GET /notes/search/suggest) that tests expect\n3. **Tests Indicate Expected Features**:\n   - Full-text search with snippet extraction and marking\n   - Relevance ranking\n   - Pagination\n   - Autocomplete suggestions\n   - FTS5 synchronization triggers\n\n4. **Database Design**:\n   - Single notes table with JSON tags\n   - Timestamps with datetime('now')\n   - WAL mode for concurrency\n   - Foreign keys enabled\n\n5. **Architecture**:\n   - Factory pattern (createApp, createSeededApp)\n   - Middleware-based error handling\n   - Parameterized queries throughout\n   - 45 diverse seed notes for testing\n\nAll source files have been fully examined and their complete contents are documented above."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab53adc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44279\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 98393</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"117b8781-6b8a-4a7e-b4f6-e4cbafd03d86","uuid":"905c90b6-e555-4c0d-99f6-2171dad27aa1","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Express + SQLite note-taking API project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. Full directory structure\n2. Contents of all source files: src/db.ts, src/models.ts, src/routes.ts, src/errors.ts, src/server.ts, src/seed.ts\n3. Contents of test files: tests/notes.test.ts, tests/search.test.ts\n4. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n5. tsconfig.json configuration\n\nRead ALL of these files completely and report their full contents. This is critical - I need every line.","agentId":"ab53adc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the entire project. Here's a comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts              (Database setup & seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts          (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts          (Express routes for CRUD)\n│   ├── errors.ts          (Error handling)\n│   ├── server.ts          (Express app factory)\n│   └── seed.ts            (Database seeding script)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts      (CRUD tests)\n│   └── search.test.ts     (Full-text search tests)\n├── package.json           (Dependencies & scripts)\n├── tsconfig.json          (TypeScript config)\n├── vitest.config.ts       (Testing framework config)\n└── .eslintrc.cjs          (Linting config)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. package.json\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- ES modules enabled (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- Core: Express 4.21 + better-sqlite3 11.0\n- Testing: Vitest 2.0 + Supertest 7.0\n- Scripts: build, lint, test, seed\n\n---\n\n### 3. tsconfig.json\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Generates source maps and declaration files\n- Excludes tests from build\n\n---\n\n### 4. src/db.ts - Database Setup\n\n**Complete Contents:**\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createDatabase(path?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = path ? new Database(path) : new Database(':memory:');\n\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  // Create notes table\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      title TEXT NOT NULL,\n      body TEXT NOT NULL,\n      tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n      created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n      updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport function seedDatabase(db: Database.Database): void {\n  const insert = db.prepare(`\n    INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n  `);\n\n  const notes = getSeedNotes();\n\n  const insertMany = db.transaction((items: { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[]) => {\n    for (const item of items) {\n      insert.run(item.title, item.body, item.tags);\n    }\n  });\n\n  insertMany(notes);\n}\n\nfunction getSeedNotes(): { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[] {\n  return [\n    {\n      title: 'Getting Started with TypeScript',\n      body: 'TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. It adds optional static typing and class-based object-oriented programming to the language. TypeScript is designed for development of large applications and transcompiles to JavaScript.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'typescript', 'javascript']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Introduction to Python Programming',\n      body: 'Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It supports multiple programming paradigms including procedural, object-oriented, and functional programming. Python is widely used in web development, data science, and automation.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'python']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Understanding Database Indexing',\n      body: 'Database indexing is a data structure technique used to quickly locate and access data in a database. Indexes are created using columns that are frequently searched against. Without an index, the database must scan every row to find relevant data, which becomes slow for large tables.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['database', 'performance']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Homemade Pasta Recipe',\n      body: 'Making fresh pasta at home is surprisingly simple. You need flour, eggs, salt, and olive oil. Mix the ingredients to form a dough, knead for 10 minutes until smooth, rest for 30 minutes, then roll out and cut into your desired shape. Cook in boiling salted water for 2-3 minutes.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'recipes', 'italian']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies',\n      body: 'The perfect chocolate chip cookie requires butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, flour, baking soda, salt, and chocolate chips. Cream the butter and sugars, add eggs and vanilla, mix in dry ingredients, fold in chocolate chips, and bake at 375°F for 9-11 minutes.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'recipes', 'baking']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Travel Guide: Tokyo Japan',\n      body: 'Tokyo is a fascinating blend of ultramodern and traditional. Visit the ancient Senso-ji temple, explore the bustling streets of Shibuya, enjoy fresh sushi at Tsukiji fish market, and experience the tranquility of Meiji Shrine. The best time to visit is during cherry blossom season in spring.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'japan', 'asia']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Exploring Paris France',\n      body: 'Paris, the City of Light, offers world-class museums like the Louvre, iconic landmarks like the Eiffel Tower, charming neighborhoods like Montmartre, and exquisite cuisine. Stroll along the Seine, visit Notre-Dame Cathedral, and enjoy croissants at a sidewalk cafe.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'france', 'europe']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Quantum Computing Basics',\n      body: 'Quantum computing leverages quantum mechanical phenomena like superposition and entanglement to process information. Unlike classical bits that are either 0 or 1, quantum bits (qubits) can exist in multiple states simultaneously. This enables quantum computers to solve certain problems exponentially faster.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'computing', 'physics']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'The Solar System Overview',\n      body: 'Our solar system consists of the Sun and everything that orbits it, including eight planets, dwarf planets, moons, asteroids, and comets. The inner planets (Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars) are rocky, while the outer planets (Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune) are gas or ice giants.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'astronomy', 'space']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Learning Guitar for Beginners',\n      body: 'Starting guitar requires patience and practice. Begin with basic open chords like G, C, D, E minor, and A minor. Practice transitioning between chords smoothly. Learn simple strumming patterns and work on finger strength. Playing just 15 minutes daily will show remarkable progress within weeks.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['music', 'guitar', 'learning']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'History of Jazz Music',\n      body: 'Jazz originated in the African-American communities of New Orleans in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. It blends elements of blues, ragtime, and European harmony. Key figures include Louis Armstrong, Duke Ellington, Charlie Parker, and Miles Davis. Jazz has evolved through many styles including swing, bebop, and fusion.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['music', 'history', 'jazz']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'React Hooks Deep Dive',\n      body: 'React Hooks allow you to use state and other React features without writing class components. useState manages local state, useEffect handles side effects, useContext accesses context, and useMemo optimizes performance. Custom hooks let you extract reusable stateful logic.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'react', 'javascript']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Docker Container Essentials',\n      body: 'Docker containers package applications with their dependencies into standardized units for development, shipment, and deployment. Containers are lightweight, portable, and consistent across environments. Key concepts include images, containers, volumes, networks, and docker-compose for multi-container applications.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'devops', 'docker']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Mediterranean Diet Benefits',\n      body: 'The Mediterranean diet emphasizes fruits, vegetables, whole grains, legumes, nuts, and olive oil. It includes moderate amounts of fish, poultry, and dairy, with limited red meat. Studies show it reduces risk of heart disease, stroke, type 2 diabetes, and cognitive decline.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'nutrition', 'diet']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Yoga for Stress Relief',\n      body: 'Yoga combines physical postures, breathing exercises, and meditation to promote relaxation and reduce stress. Regular practice improves flexibility, strength, and mental clarity. Beginner-friendly poses include child pose, downward dog, warrior I and II, and tree pose.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'fitness', 'yoga']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Machine Learning Fundamentals',\n      body: 'Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence where algorithms learn patterns from data without being explicitly programmed. Key types include supervised learning (classification, regression), unsupervised learning (clustering), and reinforcement learning. Popular frameworks include TensorFlow, PyTorch, and scikit-learn.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'ai', 'machine-learning']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Backpacking Through Southeast Asia',\n      body: 'Southeast Asia offers incredible backpacking experiences on a budget. Visit ancient temples in Cambodia, pristine beaches in Thailand, rice terraces in Vietnam, and vibrant cities in Malaysia. Budget around $30-50 per day for accommodation, food, and transport.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'asia', 'backpacking']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Sourdough Bread Baking Guide',\n      body: 'Sourdough bread requires a mature starter, flour, water, and salt. The process involves mixing, autolyse, bulk fermentation with stretch and folds, shaping, cold retard overnight, and baking in a Dutch oven. The natural fermentation creates complex flavors and better digestibility.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'baking', 'bread']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Introduction to Rust Programming',\n      body: 'Rust is a systems programming language focused on safety, speed, and concurrency. Its ownership system prevents null pointer dereferences, dangling pointers, and data races at compile time. Rust is ideal for performance-critical applications, web assembly, and embedded systems.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'rust', 'systems']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Climate Change and Renewable Energy',\n      body: 'Renewable energy sources like solar, wind, hydroelectric, and geothermal are essential for combating climate change. Solar panel costs have dropped 89% since 2010. Wind energy is the fastest-growing power source globally. Transitioning to renewables can significantly reduce greenhouse gas emissions.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['science', 'environment', 'energy']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Photography Composition Techniques',\n      body: 'Great photography relies on strong composition. The rule of thirds places subjects at grid intersections. Leading lines guide the viewer eye. Framing uses natural elements to surround the subject. Symmetry creates balance. Negative space emphasizes the main subject by leaving empty areas.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['photography', 'art', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'GraphQL vs REST API Design',\n      body: 'GraphQL lets clients request exactly the data they need in a single query, reducing over-fetching and under-fetching common with REST. REST uses multiple endpoints with fixed data structures. GraphQL has a single endpoint with a flexible query language. Both have tradeoffs in caching, complexity, and tooling.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'api', 'web']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'The Art of French Cooking',\n      body: 'French cuisine is built on foundational techniques: the five mother sauces (bechamel, veloute, espagnole, hollandaise, tomato), proper knife skills, stock making, and mastering heat control. Classic dishes include coq au vin, beef bourguignon, ratatouille, and creme brulee.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'french', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Hiking the Appalachian Trail',\n      body: 'The Appalachian Trail stretches 2,190 miles from Georgia to Maine through 14 states. Thru-hiking takes 5-7 months. Section hiking is popular for those with less time. Essential gear includes a quality backpack, lightweight tent, sleeping bag, water filter, and proper hiking boots.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'hiking', 'outdoors']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Kubernetes Orchestration Guide',\n      body: 'Kubernetes automates deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications. Key concepts include pods, services, deployments, namespaces, and ingress controllers. Kubernetes provides self-healing, horizontal scaling, rolling updates, and service discovery out of the box.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'devops', 'kubernetes']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Classical Music Appreciation',\n      body: 'Classical music spans centuries from Bach and Handel through Mozart and Beethoven to modern composers. The orchestra typically includes strings, woodwinds, brass, and percussion sections. Major forms include symphonies, concertos, sonatas, and operas. Listening actively to different sections enhances appreciation.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['music', 'classical', 'culture']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Effective Public Speaking',\n      body: 'Great public speakers master preparation, delivery, and audience engagement. Structure talks with a hook, three main points, and a memorable closing. Use pauses for emphasis, vary your tone, maintain eye contact, and use gestures naturally. Practice extensively and seek feedback.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['communication', 'skills', 'career']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Indoor Plant Care Essentials',\n      body: 'Successful indoor gardening requires understanding light, water, and soil needs. Low-light plants like pothos and snake plants are great for beginners. Water when the top inch of soil is dry. Use well-draining potting mix. Fertilize monthly during growing season. Monitor for pests regularly.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['gardening', 'plants', 'home']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'SQLite Full-Text Search Tutorial',\n      body: 'SQLite FTS5 provides powerful full-text search capabilities. Create a virtual table using FTS5, insert content, and query using the MATCH operator. FTS5 supports phrase queries, prefix queries, boolean operators, and ranking with BM25. Snippet extraction highlights matching terms in results.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'database', 'sqlite']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Mindfulness Meditation Practice',\n      body: 'Mindfulness meditation involves focusing attention on the present moment without judgment. Start with 5-minute sessions, focusing on breath. When thoughts arise, acknowledge them and return to breathing. Regular practice reduces anxiety, improves focus, and promotes emotional resilience.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'meditation', 'wellness']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Web Accessibility Standards',\n      body: 'Web accessibility ensures websites are usable by people with disabilities. Follow WCAG guidelines: provide alt text for images, ensure keyboard navigation, use semantic HTML, maintain sufficient color contrast, add ARIA labels, and test with screen readers. Accessibility benefits all users.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'web', 'accessibility']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Italian Risotto Masterclass',\n      body: 'Perfect risotto requires Arborio or Carnaroli rice, warm stock, patience, and constant stirring. Toast the rice in butter, add wine, then ladle warm stock gradually while stirring. The starch releases slowly, creating a creamy texture. Finish with butter and Parmigiano-Reggiano.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'italian', 'recipes']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Artificial Neural Networks Explained',\n      body: 'Neural networks are computing systems inspired by biological neural networks. They consist of layers of interconnected nodes (neurons) that process information. Deep learning uses many hidden layers to learn hierarchical representations. Applications include image recognition, natural language processing, and autonomous vehicles.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'ai', 'deep-learning']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Sustainable Living Tips',\n      body: 'Reduce your environmental footprint by minimizing single-use plastics, composting food waste, choosing renewable energy, buying local produce, reducing water usage, and using public transport or cycling. Small daily choices collectively make a significant environmental impact.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['environment', 'lifestyle', 'sustainability']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Chess Strategy for Intermediates',\n      body: 'Improve your chess by studying openings, understanding pawn structure, controlling the center, developing pieces early, and thinking several moves ahead. Learn tactical patterns like pins, forks, skewers, and discovered attacks. Analyze your games to identify mistakes and patterns.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['games', 'chess', 'strategy']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'RESTful API Best Practices',\n      body: 'Design RESTful APIs with consistent naming conventions, proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE), meaningful status codes, pagination for collections, versioning, authentication, and comprehensive error responses. Use JSON for request and response bodies. Document with OpenAPI specification.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'api', 'rest']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Nordic Hiking Adventures',\n      body: 'Scandinavia offers breathtaking hiking through fjords, mountains, and arctic landscapes. Norway Trolltunga and Preikestolen are iconic. Sweden Kungsleden trail spans 270 miles. Finland offers midnight sun hiking in summer. Pack layers, waterproof gear, and be prepared for rapidly changing weather.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'hiking', 'europe']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Espresso Brewing Techniques',\n      body: 'Perfect espresso requires freshly roasted beans, proper grind size, correct dose (18-20g), consistent tamping pressure, water temperature around 200°F, and 25-30 second extraction time. The result should be a balanced shot with a rich crema layer. Adjust grind size to control flow rate.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'coffee', 'techniques']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Version Control with Git',\n      body: 'Git is the most widely used version control system. Key commands include init, clone